{
  "text": "Given a real signal f (t) which can be, e.g., one coordinate of the system (one position or one momentum for instance), two methods are used to compute a time-frequency (denoted u -\u03be) representation of f : windowed Fourier transform and continuous wavelet transform. We assume that we have computed the trajectory for all times t \u2208 R. The effect of finite time interval is analyzed in Appendix B. For more details on time-frequency analysis, we refer to Refs. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] ",
